The paper deals with the $k$-means cost function, which is a fundamental problem in data science and machine learning. The paper provides upper and lower bounds on the cost of the optimal $k$-means solution, and discusses applications of these bounds. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. 

The paper also discusses the $k$-median problem in arbitrary metrics and gives bounds in terms of the doubling dimension of the metric. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-categories. 

Finally, the paper discusses the $D^2$-sampling algorithm, which is a well-known seeding procedure for the $k$-means problem. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-category, which deals with algorithms and models for social and information networks.
